<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AFC 00903 - Front Axle Codes 02ADD (Chatham Only), 02ADE (Chatham Only), and 02AED Toe-In Out of
        Specification on 4x2 and 6x4 8000 and 9000i Models
    </stitle>
    <afc id="afc00903">
        <afcnum>00903</afcnum>
        <afcdate>March, 2000</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>FRONT AXLE</subjectfile>
        <subject>Front Axle Codes 02ADD (Chatham Only), 02ADE (Chatham Only), and 02AED Toe-In Out of Specification on
            4x2 and 6x4 8000 and 9000i Models
        </subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>8100</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8200</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>8300</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9000i</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>02ADD</ucode>
                <ucode>02ADE</ucode>
                <ucode>02AED</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The toe-in specification was incorrectly set by the vendor for front axle Codes 02ADD and 02ADE,
                    used in 9000i Models built in Chatham between November 1, 1999 and December 8, 1999 and front axle
                    Code 02AED, used in 8000 and 9000i Models built in Chatham, Garland and Springfield between October
                    1, 1999 and December 15, 1999.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>If the axle toe-in was not previously corrected, reset the toe-in to 1/16 inch +/- 1/16 inch following
                the toe-in procedure outlined in Service Manual Section CTS-5027K, page 13 section 7.1., found in Group
                02 of the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Toe-in should be reset only by trained technicians. When electronic equipment is used to set
                        toe-in, equipment must be in calibration to insure reading accuracy.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Tighten the tie rod end clamp bolts following the information in Table 1.</para>
            <table id="t0090301">
                <title>Tie Rod End Clamp Bolt Tightening Specification</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="4.70in"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Axle Code</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Bolt Tightening Specification</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" morerows="1">
                                <para>02ADD</para>
                                <para>02ADE</para>
                                <para>02AED</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Straight Tie Rod Ends: 45 to 60 Ft-lbs. (61 to 81 Nm)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Drop Tie Rod Ends: 55 to 70 Ft-lbs. (75 to 95 Nm)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
        <laborinfo>
            <para>Operation number from Table 2 must appear on all warranty claims.</para>
            <table id="t0090302">
                <title>Labor Information</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.47in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="3.01in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.57in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Operation No.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Description</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Time</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>A40-00903-1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Adjust Toe-In</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                <para>0.7 Hr.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </laborinfo>
        <claims>
            <para>
                <title>ADMINISTRATIVE PROCEDURE</title>
            </para>
            <para>Expense is to be charged to Warranty.
                <hotlnk xrefid="afclaim">Claims</hotlnk>
                are to be submitted in the normal manner, making reference to Authorized Field Change Number G-00903.
            </para>
            <para>It is important that the coding be completed properly to assist in processing the warranty claim.
                Complete instructions will be found in the Warranty Manual, Section 7-1. Special attention should be
                given to Items 39 through 44.
            </para>
            <para>To assure this important improvement is made in a timely manner, all claims for G-00903 activity must
                be submitted by March 31, 2001 or within the normal warranty period for the vehicle, if after March 31,
                2001.
            </para>
            <figure id="afclaim" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/afclaim.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
            </figure>
        </claims>
    </afc>
</isis>
